--- [RESPONSE] (10.1s) ---
### File Structure
```
jobboard/
│
├── app.py
├── data/
│   ├── jobs.txt
│   ├── companies.txt
│   ├── categories.txt
│   ├── applications.txt
│   ├── resumes.txt
│   └── job_categories.txt
│
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── job_listings.html
│   ├── job_details.html
│   ├── application_form.html
│   ├── application_tracking.html
│   ├── companies_directory.html
│   ├── company_profile.html
│   ├── resume_management.html
│   └── search_results.html
│
└── static/
    ├── css/
    │   └── styles.css
    ├── js/
    │   └── scripts.js
    └── uploads/
        └── resumes/
```

### File Descriptions
```
app.py
- The main backend Python file implementing the web application using a web framework (e.g., Flask).
- Handles routing for all nine pages, data reading/writing from/to local text files in the 'data' directory.
- Implements logic for job browsing, searching, filtering, application submission, resume management, and navigation.
- Manages file uploads for resumes, and updates the corresponding text files accordingly.

data/
- Contains all the local text files storing persistent data as specified:
  - jobs.txt: Job postings data.
  - companies.txt: Company profiles data.
  - categories.txt: Job categories data.
  - applications.txt: Job applications data.
  - resumes.txt: Uploaded resumes metadata.
  - job_categories.txt: Mapping between jobs and categories.

templates/
- Contains HTML template files for each of the nine pages, structured according to the page designs and element IDs specified.
- Each template corresponds to one page:
  - dashboard.html: Dashboard page.
  - job_listings.html: Job listings with search and filters.
  - job_details.html: Detailed job information.
  - application_form.html: Job application submission form.
  - application_tracking.html: User's application tracking page.
  - companies_directory.html: Companies listing page.
  - company_profile.html: Detailed company profile page.
  - resume_management.html: Resume upload and management page.
  - search_results.html: Search results for jobs and companies.

static/
- Contains static assets used by the web application:
  - css/styles.css: Stylesheet for consistent UI styling.
  - js/scripts.js: JavaScript for client-side interactivity, such as navigation and dynamic filtering.
  - uploads/resumes/: Directory to store uploaded resume files.

This structure keeps the backend logic consolidated in a single Python file for simplicity, while separating frontend templates and static assets for maintainability and clarity, fully meeting the project requirements.
```
